Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so\N{\rChinese}OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.96,0:00:06.78,English,,0,0,0,,we are starting an overview of Greek history.\N{\rChinese}...??????????????????????????????????????1?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.40,0:00:09.08,English,,0,0,0,,Remember the story so far.\N{\rChinese}?????????????????????????????????????????..?????..????????????中????????????????????????????????中?????????中???前??????????????????????????..?????..??...??..??..??..??..??..??..??..?????..??..??..???…..??…..……..?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.36,0:00:12.74,English,,0,0,0,,We talked about the Bronze Age and\N{\rChinese}我们谈到了青铜时代和
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.74,0:00:17.14,English,,0,0,0,,where Mycenaean Greece was trading\N{\rChinese}米凯尼希腊的希腊交易与世界的交流与战斗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.14,0:00:19.42,English,,0,0,0,,and fighting with the rest of the world.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.70,0:00:22.40,English,,0,0,0,,And then the Bronze Age collapse happened and\N{\rChinese}And then the Bronze Age collapse happened and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.40,0:00:24.68,English,,0,0,0,,Mycenaean Greece came to an end.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.68,0:00:26.66,English,,0,0,0,,And because of its destruction,\N{\rChinese}??
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.02,0:00:31.28,English,,0,0,0,,this allowed for massive innovation throughout Greece.\N{\rChinese}这使得希腊全境大创新
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.50,0:00:34.48,English,,0,0,0,,So we saw the introduction of the polis, the city -state.\N{\rChinese}这时出现了古希腊的城邦
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.78,0:00:40.70,English,,0,0,0,,We saw the beginning of the use of the alphabet.\N{\rChinese}我们见证了文字使用的起始。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.32,0:00:46.28,English,,0,0,0,,And so literacy rates increased radically throughout Greece.\N{\rChinese}于是，文字普及全希腊，文字率大增。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.58,0:00:50.22,English,,0,0,0,,And we saw Homer who gave us the Iliad\N{\rChinese}我们看见了荷马的《伊利亚》与《奥德赛》。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.22,0:00:52.02,English,,0,0,0,,and the Odyssey.\N{\rChinese}我们看见了荷尔曼的...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.00,0:00:54.52,English,,0,0,0,,So today,\N{\rChinese}译文1
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.68,0:01:00.62,English,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to go over the overview of Greek history,\N{\rChinese}译文2
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.78,0:01:02.72,English,,0,0,0,,mainly focusing on the polis.\N{\rChinese}主要以城邦为中心。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.22,0:01:07.62,English,,0,0,0,,So one thing to understand about the polis is\N{\rChinese}翻译后句子句后再加上?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.62,0:01:11.32,English,,0,0,0,,that geography is destiny.\N{\rChinese}那地理决定命运。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.58,0:01:16.50,English,,0,0,0,,Geography is destiny.\N{\rChinese}地理决定命运。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.70,0:01:19.42,English,,0,0,0,,And this basically means that\N{\rChinese}并且这基本意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.42,0:01:24.40,English,,0,0,0,,your geography will determine the culture,\N{\rChinese}你的地理会决定文化
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.68,0:01:26.70,English,,0,0,0,,the economy, and\N{\rChinese}经济与
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.70,0:01:29.70,English,,0,0,0,,the political structure of your society.\N{\rChinese}你的社会的政治结构。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:32.76,English,,0,0,0,,And we see that with the Greek polis.\N{\rChinese}我们在希腊的古典里看到的。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.02,0:01:35.32,English,,0,0,0,,The Greek geography is very diverse.\N{\rChinese}希腊的地理很大。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.56,0:01:38.08,English,,0,0,0,,There are mountains, there are rivers,\N{\rChinese}28. 这里有山脉，河流，平原与河岸。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.24,0:01:41.34,English,,0,0,0,,there are plains, and there are coastlines.\N{\rChinese}29. 28????????????????????????????????????
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.06,0:01:44.50,English,,0,0,0,,And depending on where\N{\rChinese}]\}We need to translate cues 28-30. They are: [28] There are mountains, there are rivers, [29] there are plains, and there are coastlines. [30] Anddepending on where ... (incomplete). We need to produce translations array with 3 strings. Use Chinese terms: 山脉, 河流, 平原, 河岸? but earlier they used
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.50,0:01:46.36,English,,0,0,0,,you are geographically in Greece,\N{\rChinese}你在地理上位于希腊，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.58,0:01:49.86,English,,0,0,0,,you will have a different type of polis.\N{\rChinese}你会有不同的古典里。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:54.04,English,,0,0,0,,And so the two classic examples are Sparta and Athens.\N{\rChinese}两者皆是古典里的两种典型。”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.68,0:02:00.46,English,,0,0,0,,Sparta and Athens are the two most dominant polis in about the year 500 BC.\N{\rChinese}???
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.72,0:02:04.38,English,,0,0,0,,So let's first talk about Sparta.\N{\rChinese}???
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.80,0:02:09.92,English,,0,0,0,,So Sparta is located on the Pelonese.\N{\rChinese}???
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.54,0:02:11.84,English,,0,0,0,,This is Sparta.\N{\rChinese}这是萨尔帕。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.62,0:02:18.34,English,,0,0,0,,And the land around Sparta is basically plains,\N{\rChinese}萨尔帕周围的土地基本是平原，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.60,0:02:21.20,English,,0,0,0,,which makes it ideal for agriculture.\N{\rChinese}它们的土壤好好。”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.60,0:02:24.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So for most of its history,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以在它的历史大部分时间里，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.02,0:02:29.18,English,,0,0,0,,Sparta was an agricultural nation.\N{\rChinese}萨尔帕是一个农业国。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.30,0:02:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,And because\N{\rChinese}而且因为
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.66,0:02:35.78,English,,0,0,0,,it is ideal for agriculture,\N{\rChinese}它是农业的理想之地，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.08,0:02:38.70,English,,0,0,0,,it needs people to work the land.\N{\rChinese}它需要人们去工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.10,0:02:41.52,English,,0,0,0,,And through its conquest,\N{\rChinese}And through itsconquest,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.00,0:02:44.90,English,,0,0,0,,Sparta developed a slave system.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.22,0:02:47.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And these people are called helots.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.48,0:02:51.08,English,,0,0,0,,And helots are just slaves in Sparta\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.08,0:02:52.86,English,,0,0,0,,that work the land. They are farmers.\N{\rChinese}它们在耕地，农民们。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.16,0:02:56.64,English,,0,0,0,,And these are people who have been conquered by Sparta.\N{\rChinese}这些人是被塞尔帕斯特拉的夺取。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.66,0:03:01.76,English,,0,0,0,,And because there are so many helots, okay, the ratio is about 10 to 1.\N{\rChinese}因为它们有点儿…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.00,0:03:06.38,English,,0,0,0,,So for every one helot, sorry, for every one Spartan, there's 10 helots.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.98,0:03:11.98,English,,0,0,0,,Sparta had to become a military society in order to control the helots.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.84,0:03:16.86,English,,0,0,0,,So it created an education system in\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.86,0:03:20.36,English,,0,0,0,,order to train its citizens to be soldiers.\N{\rChinese}以训练其公民成为士兵的目的。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.36,0:03:22.80,English,,0,0,0,,So the system worked like this.\N{\rChinese}在此系统中，已然。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.46,0:03:27.00,English,,0,0,0,,About age 7, you left your family\N{\rChinese}大约七岁时，离开了家…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:30.34,English,,0,0,0,,and you were put into a boarding school where\N{\rChinese}在此时，您被送进了寄宿学校，那里…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.34,0:03:34.24,English,,0,0,0,,you were watched over by kids who were older than you.\N{\rChinese}在此时……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.38,0:03:35.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Maybe 11 or 12.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:39.46,English,,0,0,0,,And obviously, you put young kids with older kids,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.64,0:03:43.42,English,,0,0,0,,the older kids will beat the crap out of these young kids\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.42,0:03:45.60,English,,0,0,0,,who are about 7 or 8. And\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.60,0:03:50.34,English,,0,0,0,,this instills the idea of emotional discipline into the system.\N{\rChinese}这为系统注入了情感纪律的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.34,0:03:54.72,English,,0,0,0,,And this is what happened to the children. Now, when these children became teenagers,\N{\rChinese}现在当时光回到后期……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.20,0:03:58.96,English,,0,0,0,,they were paired with a mentor\N{\rChinese}………
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.96,0:04:02.64,English,,0,0,0,,who was maybe 25 to about 30, okay?\N{\rChinese}大约25到30岁，没错？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.74,0:04:05.64,English,,0,0,0,,An older adult. And they became lovers.\N{\rChinese}一位年长的成年人。随后他们成了恋人。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.64,0:04:11.10,English,,0,0,0,,The Spartans did not consider this homosexuality.\N{\rChinese}斯巴达人把它视作同一人间的情感联结。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.16,0:04:12.56,English,,0,0,0,,We would consider it homosexuality.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.60,0:04:15.44,English,,0,0,0,,But they themselves did not consider this homosexuality.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:17.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They just considered this as a\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.72,0:04:21.78,English,,0,0,0,,way to build emotional cohesion,\N{\rChinese}73. 方式构建情感连结，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.08,0:04:25.38,English,,0,0,0,,love among its soldiers.\N{\rChinese}74. 其士兵间的情感情绪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.66,0:04:28.64,English,,0,0,0,,And about age 18 or 19,\N{\rChinese}5. 约18岁/??
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.16,0:04:31.78,English,,0,0,0,,the students would graduate and\N{\rChinese}学生们毕业后会这样，他们会去结婚并组建自己的家庭。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.78,0:04:36.10,English,,0,0,0,,they would go on to marry and have their own families.\N{\rChinese}但斯巴达士兵们都要一起吃饭。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.68,0:04:41.26,English,,0,0,0,,But the Spartan soldiers were all required to eat together.\N{\rChinese}But the Spartan soldiers wereall required to eat together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.64,0:04:45.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the soldiers, even though they had families, they were still required to eat together.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以士兵们即使他们有家人，也仍需一起吃饭。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.68,0:04:47.64,English,,0,0,0,,They were required to train together and to eat together.\N{\rChinese}他们又要训练一同，吃一同。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.36,0:04:52.48,English,,0,0,0,,Spartans had no private property.\N{\rChinese}斯巴达士兵们没得有私财。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.72,0:04:56.92,English,,0,0,0,,Everything, including the helots, belonged to everyone.\N{\rChinese}Everything, including the helots, belonged to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.24,0:05:00.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So it's basically like communism or proto -communism.\N{\rChinese}好的？它就是像百思通的百思通？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:01.94,English,,0,0,0,,They had no money system.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.14,0:05:06.48,English,,0,0,0,,They had no wealth. Everything belonged to everyone.\N{\rChinese}他们没有财富。全都归大家。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.48,0:05:10.02,English,,0,0,0,,And it was a brutal state.\N{\rChinese}它是个繁忙的州
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.22,0:05:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,The Spartans were notorious for being brutal people.\N{\rChinese}斯巴达人以其繁忙的方式而闻名。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.48,0:05:17.36,English,,0,0,0,,So an example is the helots.\N{\rChinese}斯巴达人以此例为其繁忙的能量。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.58,0:05:22.98,English,,0,0,0,,So they had a campaign of terror to maintain control over the helots.\N{\rChinese}So they had a campaign of terror to maintain control over the helots.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.30,0:05:27.18,English,,0,0,0,,So young soldiers would often be\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.18,0:05:30.72,English,,0,0,0,,required to patrol at night.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.26,0:05:33.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They would maybe lie in the fields.\N{\rChinese}Okay? 他们可能在田里休息
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.14,0:05:37.62,English,,0,0,0,,Because now and then, some helots would break curfew.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.76,0:05:40.82,English,,0,0,0,,They would, at midnight, try to sneak out and have some fun.\N{\rChinese}They would, at midnight, try to sneak out and have some fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.06,0:05:43.70,English,,0,0,0,,And if you, as a Spartan young man,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.80,0:05:48.04,English,,0,0,0,,saw a Spartan, you would say, I saw a helot be out at night.\N{\rChinese}saw a Spartan, you would say,I saw a helot be out at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.34,0:05:49.74,English,,0,0,0,,Well, they would kill you.\N{\rChinese}好的，先前的字幕翻译已完成。请在此处翻译以下字幕：
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.76,0:05:52.74,English,,0,0,0,,They would take out a knife and stab you in the neck. Okay? And\N{\rChinese}翻译后可用来回到?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:55.46,English,,0,0,0,,this was meant to instill terror\N{\rChinese}这个词句...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.46,0:05:59.54,English,,0,0,0,,in the helots to prevent them from rebelling.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.70,0:06:02.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But the problem is, because there were so\N{\rChinese}好的，...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.74,0:06:05.54,English,,0,0,0,,many helots, and the Spartans were so brutal,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.24,0:06:08.80,English,,0,0,0,,rebellions and revolutions would break out often.\N{\rChinese}rebellions and revolutions would break out often.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.46,0:06:12.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So this created a society\N{\rChinese}OK? 这句...??
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.02,0:06:14.44,English,,0,0,0,,which focused on the helots.\N{\rChinese}翻译...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.44,0:06:18.38,English,,0,0,0,,And this focused on maintaining control in the Pelonese.\N{\rChinese}??
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.66,0:06:23.90,English,,0,0,0,,So the Spartans were not at all interested in foreign policy.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.06,0:06:28.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They had absolutely no interest in the world outside Sparta.\N{\rChinese}OK? 这句...??
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.14,0:06:33.32,English,,0,0,0,,The Spartans, as a culture, was very conservative.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:36.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They liked the way that...\N{\rChinese}OK? 这句...??
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.10,0:06:38.10,English,,0,0,0,,They liked the way...\N{\rChinese}他们喜欢那种方式...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.24,0:06:42.38,English,,0,0,0,,They wanted things to stay the way...\N{\rChinese}他们想要让它们保持那样的...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.14,0:06:48.16,English,,0,0,0,,They are. So it was a very conformist culture.\N{\rChinese}他们是的。所以它是一种非常符合的文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.74,0:06:54.50,English,,0,0,0,,Now and then you had some kings or individuals\N{\rChinese}现在...??
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.50,0:06:55.74,English,,0,0,0,,who tried to change society.\N{\rChinese}谁尝试改变社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:06:58.24,English,,0,0,0,,The Spartans would kill those people.\N{\rChinese}斯巴达人会杀死那些人。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.34,0:07:02.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You were not allowed to question authority.\N{\rChinese}好的？你们不允许提问权威。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.02,0:07:05.80,English,,0,0,0,,You were not allowed to promote change in Sparta.\N{\rChinese}好的，...??
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.28,0:07:08.76,English,,0,0,0,,The Spartans were also isolationists.\N{\rChinese}斯巴达人也是孤立主义者。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.84,0:07:12.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Their entire society was a society of isolationists.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们的整个社会是孤立主义者的社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.36,0:07:15.34,English,,0,0,0,,Their entire policy was, if you leave us alone, we'll leave you alone.\N{\rChinese}他们的全部政策是：如果你们把我们留着，我们就把你们留着。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.22,0:07:18.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And so that\N{\rChinese}OK? 这就是…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.04,0:07:21.78,English,,0,0,0,,was the society of Sparta.\N{\rChinese}是斯巴达的社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.38,0:07:24.12,English,,0,0,0,,When you think about it, in many ways,\N{\rChinese}当你思考时，在多种方式里，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.42,0:07:28.18,English,,0,0,0,,it's very much like China throughout its history.\N{\rChinese}它在历史上很久的相似。”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.38,0:07:31.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the analogy is China,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以这个类比是中国，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.48,0:07:34.70,English,,0,0,0,,which China has always been, throughout its history,\N{\rChinese}中国在整个历史里一直如此，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.82,0:07:36.64,English,,0,0,0,,very conservative and very isolationist.\N{\rChinese}非常保守且很久久的孤立主义者。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.88,0:07:39.96,English,,0,0,0,,China is just not interested in the outside world. Why? Because\N{\rChinese}中国只是在点儿…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.96,0:07:42.14,English,,0,0,0,,it's focused on maintaining\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:46.68,English,,0,0,0,,control over its peasantry.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.84,0:07:49.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There's too much internal chaos.\N{\rChinese}好的？内部混乱太多了。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.06,0:07:52.68,English,,0,0,0,,China just is not interested in the outside world.\N{\rChinese}中国只是不关心外部世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.92,0:07:57.32,English,,0,0,0,,So China, for its history, has both been conservative, does not like change.\N{\rChinese}所以说中国在历史上既保守又不喜欢变革。
